1
00:00:03,590 --> 00:00:06,080
- Ouji?
- Let's break up.

2
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:15,950
Sorry.

3
00:00:17,160 --> 00:00:19,080
I'm just... sorry.

4
00:00:21,930 --> 00:00:26,430
Haru, I think you're cute, and I cherish you.

5
00:00:30,130 --> 00:00:33,360
But my body refuses to respond.

6
00:00:35,930 --> 00:00:42,000
I haven't been able to get it up,
with anyone.

7
00:00:47,910 --> 00:00:50,030
Get it... up?

8
00:00:53,610 --> 00:00:58,380
Well... I know there are remedies.

9
00:00:58,380 --> 00:01:01,100
I've heard about them before.

10
00:01:01,100 --> 00:01:03,390
I can help look into it.

11
00:01:04,150 --> 00:01:07,010
Mind if I take a smoke?

12
00:01:22,910 --> 00:01:25,450
It's freezing out here.

13
00:01:43,830 --> 00:01:45,500
Thanks.

14
00:01:52,450 --> 00:01:58,050
It was boiling during our ceremony.
Has it been half a year already?

15
00:01:59,800 --> 00:02:03,510
It's been about three months.

16
00:02:04,940 --> 00:02:06,700
Oh.

17
00:02:09,210 --> 00:02:12,510
Guess I'm finally paying the price, huh?

18
00:02:12,510 --> 00:02:14,240
What?

19
00:02:14,240 --> 00:02:20,100
I've never actually enjoyed sex before.

20
00:02:20,100 --> 00:02:21,260
What?

21
00:02:21,260 --> 00:02:23,200
Ouch, my ear.

22
00:02:23,200 --> 00:02:25,690
Sorry, it's just...

23
00:02:25,690 --> 00:02:30,350
I became insanely popular
when I debuted with the band.

24
00:02:30,350 --> 00:02:33,160
Sure, at first I let myself bask in it.

25
00:02:33,160 --> 00:02:35,050
But over time...

26
00:02:36,720 --> 00:02:39,280
Girls would imagine their own versions of me,

27
00:02:39,280 --> 00:02:42,700
and come at me aggressively
in the name of "love".

28
00:02:42,700 --> 00:02:45,510
Eventually, I got fed up with it all.

29
00:02:47,500 --> 00:02:51,170
I couldn't stand these girls
having their way with me,

30
00:02:51,170 --> 00:02:53,960
so I decided to go on the offensive
before they could.

31
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:58,040
To eat, before I was eaten, if you will.

32
00:02:59,470 --> 00:03:05,550
Repeat that cycle,
and I ultimately ran myself dry.

33
00:03:06,560 --> 00:03:09,000
Both my body and heart, emptied out.

34
00:03:11,920 --> 00:03:16,680
And then the kidney stone? Poor me.

35
00:03:17,720 --> 00:03:21,620
You really do reap what you sow.

36
00:03:22,510 --> 00:03:24,520
That's not...

37
00:03:25,770 --> 00:03:30,760
You came to care for me after that debacle.

38
00:03:31,540 --> 00:03:34,060
It was a huge help, sure.

39
00:03:34,060 --> 00:03:37,420
But I thought you'd ultimately ask
for the same thing,

40
00:03:37,420 --> 00:03:42,070
only to be disappointed
I had nothing to offer.

41
00:03:44,360 --> 00:03:46,320
Except, you were different.

42
00:03:47,650 --> 00:03:51,530
You made no moves.
You completely ignored my room.

43
00:03:51,530 --> 00:03:55,280
That's because your room was...

44
00:03:55,280 --> 00:03:58,100
It seriously put me at ease.

45
00:04:01,540 --> 00:04:03,600
You saved me.

46
00:04:48,060 --> 00:04:49,560
Sorry.

47
00:04:52,220 --> 00:04:54,110
Let's break up after all.

48
00:04:56,570 --> 00:04:59,640
If you stay, you won't ever get to have sex.

49
00:05:02,500 --> 00:05:04,050
No.

50
00:05:05,540 --> 00:05:07,440
I don't want to break up.

51
00:05:08,460 --> 00:05:10,600
I saved you?

52
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:11,920
Well, you saved me.

53
00:05:11,920 --> 00:05:14,090
Of course I want to stay with you.

54
00:05:14,090 --> 00:05:17,400
But don't you want to have sex?

55
00:05:20,180 --> 00:05:22,670
Sorry.

56
00:05:22,670 --> 00:05:26,530
I don't mean that in a bad way, really.

57
00:05:27,690 --> 00:05:31,820
In the end, it's all my fault.

58
00:05:34,040 --> 00:05:37,620
I won't touch you again, I promise.

59
00:05:42,620 --> 00:05:47,640
I'm sorry our marriage turned out like this.

60
00:06:55,410 --> 00:06:59,580
[Episode 6]

61
00:07:05,170 --> 00:07:08,640
<i>Sorry. Let's break up after all.</i>

62
00:07:09,560 --> 00:07:12,370
<i>If you stay, you won't ever get to have sex.</i>

63
00:07:18,560 --> 00:07:20,860
[Open Relationships]

64
00:07:20,860 --> 00:07:24,480
[Couples who consensually have sex
with other partners]

65
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:26,900
Unbelievable.

66
00:07:27,660 --> 00:07:29,410
Something the matter?

67
00:07:31,150 --> 00:07:32,650
No.

68
00:07:38,560 --> 00:07:43,310
<i>I'm sorry our marriage turned out like this.</i>

69
00:07:47,740 --> 00:07:50,290
What the hell, man?

70
00:07:50,290 --> 00:07:55,090
Got into an argument with Haru?

71
00:07:55,090 --> 00:07:58,030
If only it were an argument.

72
00:08:04,230 --> 00:08:06,440
What? He left?

73
00:08:06,440 --> 00:08:08,080
When?

74
00:08:09,430 --> 00:08:12,310
About a week ago.

75
00:08:12,310 --> 00:08:16,200
Is this leading up to a divorce?

76
00:08:18,950 --> 00:08:22,040
Sorry, I shouldn't be so blunt.

77
00:08:22,040 --> 00:08:27,200
When he asked to break up,
did he mean a divorce?

78
00:08:27,200 --> 00:08:29,440
That's usually what it means, yes.

79
00:08:29,440 --> 00:08:31,650
Thought so.

80
00:08:32,490 --> 00:08:36,990
You know, I was over the moon

81
00:08:37,700 --> 00:08:41,750
to hear Ouji say he actually liked me.

82
00:08:42,420 --> 00:08:45,870
I know. I witnessed your elation firsthand.

83
00:08:45,870 --> 00:08:48,500
Can you blame me?

84
00:08:48,500 --> 00:08:52,950
I suddenly became the heroine
after living as an extra my whole life.

85
00:08:52,950 --> 00:08:56,130
- Fair enough.
- I was speeding towards my happy end,

86
00:08:56,130 --> 00:09:00,250
as the Ouji I dreamed of turned my way.

87
00:09:00,250 --> 00:09:04,430
He chose to love me, to hug boring ol' me.

88
00:09:04,430 --> 00:09:06,520
Sounds straight out of a drama, right?

89
00:09:06,520 --> 00:09:08,040
Sure does.

90
00:09:08,040 --> 00:09:14,040
But reality looks towards what happens next.

91
00:09:15,600 --> 00:09:17,850
You won't protest the break up?

92
00:09:17,850 --> 00:09:20,650
I already told him I wanted to stay.

93
00:09:20,650 --> 00:09:24,550
Why not be more clingy about it?

94
00:09:25,250 --> 00:09:27,740
I couldn't be.

95
00:09:27,740 --> 00:09:31,030
<i>Girls would come at me aggressively
in the name of "love".</i>

96
00:09:31,030 --> 00:09:34,070
<i>Eventually, I got fed up with it all.</i>

97
00:09:35,460 --> 00:09:38,610
Because I wasn't any better.

98
00:09:39,810 --> 00:09:43,260
I was just like those people
who cornered him in the first place.

99
00:09:44,050 --> 00:09:47,030
I pushed my expectations onto him.

100
00:09:47,030 --> 00:09:52,140
You couldn't help it. You were a fan of his.

101
00:09:53,190 --> 00:09:55,620
I know that.

102
00:09:56,950 --> 00:10:03,130
But I realize now how it was suffocating him.

103
00:10:03,130 --> 00:10:06,310
You couldn't know. He never told you.

104
00:10:06,310 --> 00:10:07,820
Right?

105
00:10:07,820 --> 00:10:12,440
Anyone would think Ouji
was a romance powerhouse.

106
00:10:12,440 --> 00:10:14,030
I suppose.

107
00:10:14,030 --> 00:10:16,400
You are too, Akina.

108
00:10:17,230 --> 00:10:18,960
I guess.

109
00:10:18,960 --> 00:10:23,700
But I'm a weakling when it comes to romance.

110
00:10:23,700 --> 00:10:27,350
- That, you are.
- No need to affirm it.

111
00:10:27,350 --> 00:10:29,520
Anyway, I thought a weakling like me

112
00:10:29,520 --> 00:10:33,360
would never get through to a guy like him.

113
00:10:33,360 --> 00:10:35,880
So since he finally looked my way,

114
00:10:35,880 --> 00:10:39,710
I thought he'd notice my efforts,
and make the first move.

115
00:10:39,710 --> 00:10:40,700
How bold.

116
00:10:40,700 --> 00:10:45,840
But I guess I was pressuring him after all.

117
00:10:47,510 --> 00:10:51,580
I never once gave Ouji's feelings a thought.

118
00:10:52,750 --> 00:10:56,910
He looked like he was really struggling...

119
00:11:17,830 --> 00:11:19,480
Haru.

120
00:11:20,250 --> 00:11:22,880
To tell you the truth...

121
00:11:30,400 --> 00:11:32,210
No, never mind.

122
00:11:32,210 --> 00:11:34,000
Say...

123
00:11:35,010 --> 00:11:40,840
What does it mean to be a weakling
or powerhouse...

124
00:11:40,840 --> 00:11:42,980
when it comes to romance?

125
00:11:43,550 --> 00:11:45,350
Huh?

126
00:11:45,350 --> 00:11:48,020
Is the one who fell first the weakling?

127
00:11:48,020 --> 00:11:50,780
Is there no equality when it comes to love?

128
00:11:51,710 --> 00:11:55,620
I guess so.

129
00:11:56,960 --> 00:11:59,600
Then that makes me a fellow weakling.

130
00:12:00,180 --> 00:12:01,600
Huh?

131
00:12:01,600 --> 00:12:03,810
What?

132
00:12:04,380 --> 00:12:07,080
You've fallen for someone?

133
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:10,800
What? Akina, in love?

134
00:12:10,800 --> 00:12:14,320
Akina, who prefers sex over romance, in love?

135
00:12:14,320 --> 00:12:18,050
You could say one thing led to the other...

136
00:12:20,900 --> 00:12:22,460
A brothel?

137
00:12:22,460 --> 00:12:23,950
A brothel, like, a brothel?

138
00:12:23,950 --> 00:12:28,340
Don't make me repeat myself.
I'm just as surprised.

139
00:12:28,340 --> 00:12:31,780
You look so cute right now, Akina.

140
00:12:31,780 --> 00:12:37,900
So you fell for this "therapist"?

141
00:12:39,880 --> 00:12:43,940
I know. I know you want to call me stupid.

142
00:12:43,940 --> 00:12:49,310
No, well... Do you love him for his body?

143
00:12:50,100 --> 00:12:52,160
You don't?

144
00:12:53,200 --> 00:12:55,950
I don't know.

145
00:12:55,950 --> 00:13:00,160
Of course, he's always making me feel good.

146
00:13:00,160 --> 00:13:02,040
But I go and check his reviews,

147
00:13:02,040 --> 00:13:06,010
and feel weird knowing he does this
with other women.

148
00:13:06,010 --> 00:13:09,020
I get sad, and miss him when he leaves, too.

149
00:13:09,020 --> 00:13:10,640
So do I love him physically?

150
00:13:10,640 --> 00:13:12,780
I think it's more than that.

151
00:13:12,780 --> 00:13:14,930
Right? I thought so.

152
00:13:20,010 --> 00:13:24,920
Powerhouses can become weaklings too, okay?

153
00:13:24,920 --> 00:13:29,640
Relationships that aren't equal,
are pointless.

154
00:13:31,640 --> 00:13:37,110
So I'm seeing him again later tonight.

155
00:13:37,110 --> 00:13:38,930
What happened to it being pointless?

156
00:13:38,930 --> 00:13:40,480
They're two separate matters.

157
00:13:40,480 --> 00:13:43,430
If I have the money to see him, I'll pay.

158
00:13:45,640 --> 00:13:49,110
Akina, you're you, powerhouse or not.

159
00:13:49,110 --> 00:13:50,790
What's that supposed to mean?

160
00:13:50,790 --> 00:13:53,150
I mean, you're super cool.

161
00:14:02,180 --> 00:14:03,940
Dear.

162
00:14:04,740 --> 00:14:06,380
Dear.

163
00:14:07,020 --> 00:14:10,420
What's wrong? You're spacing out.

164
00:14:10,420 --> 00:14:12,160
Sorry.

165
00:14:12,160 --> 00:14:15,520
The sink. You're leaving it running.

166
00:14:16,440 --> 00:14:20,490
Aren't you always talking about conservation?

167
00:14:21,610 --> 00:14:22,990
Sorry.

168
00:14:25,140 --> 00:14:27,800
Are you out the entire day tomorrow?

169
00:14:27,800 --> 00:14:29,400
Yeah.

170
00:14:29,400 --> 00:14:33,300
I'll be doing makeup
for a stage play poster shoot.

171
00:14:33,300 --> 00:14:36,020
You're still doing makeup work?

172
00:14:36,020 --> 00:14:38,640
I thought you were going to look
for better gigs.

173
00:14:50,790 --> 00:14:52,260
Hello?

174
00:14:52,260 --> 00:14:55,550
Sorry, I know we promised not to call...

175
00:14:55,550 --> 00:14:58,130
It's okay. So?

176
00:14:58,130 --> 00:15:00,400
<i>It wasn't about us.</i>

177
00:15:03,050 --> 00:15:05,170
The article.

178
00:15:05,170 --> 00:15:07,070
Do you know Ryuhei Sato?

179
00:15:07,070 --> 00:15:09,520
He's often cast as a main lead.

180
00:15:10,200 --> 00:15:12,180
No, I don't think so.

181
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:15,580
I don't know who his partner was, but...

182
00:15:19,780 --> 00:15:21,440
Fuyumi?

183
00:15:23,150 --> 00:15:25,580
I hear you.

184
00:15:26,370 --> 00:15:28,300
Thank goodness.

185
00:15:28,300 --> 00:15:29,820
<i>Fuyumi.</i>

186
00:15:29,820 --> 00:15:32,210
Can we meet sometime soon?

187
00:15:32,210 --> 00:15:34,150
I want to speak to you, in person.

188
00:15:36,740 --> 00:15:39,000
I can't think about that now.

189
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:41,330
<i>Sorry, I'll text you back.</i>

190
00:15:59,390 --> 00:16:02,630
My stomach was hurting.

191
00:16:02,630 --> 00:16:04,230
I see.

192
00:16:05,320 --> 00:16:07,380
Were you speaking to someone?

193
00:16:08,210 --> 00:16:11,460
I thought I heard some voices.

194
00:16:12,510 --> 00:16:14,670
I was watching a video.

195
00:16:16,060 --> 00:16:18,840
Watch it only after you finish cleaning up.

196
00:16:20,210 --> 00:16:21,840
Sorry.

197
00:17:13,070 --> 00:17:14,870
[Naoki]

198
00:17:24,770 --> 00:17:26,950
Let me go.

199
00:17:26,950 --> 00:17:28,730
Why do you keep ignoring my texts?

200
00:17:28,730 --> 00:17:30,870
What are you talking about?

201
00:17:30,870 --> 00:17:33,550
You're the one who called me easy,

202
00:17:33,550 --> 00:17:35,110
and told me to buy a man.

203
00:17:35,110 --> 00:17:39,050
- I was only...
- Well, thanks for the great advice.

204
00:17:39,050 --> 00:17:40,830
- Huh?
- Bye.

205
00:17:40,830 --> 00:17:42,830
Wait.

206
00:17:42,830 --> 00:17:44,960
Don't tell me you actually bought a man.

207
00:17:44,960 --> 00:17:47,240
Like I said, you told me to.

208
00:17:47,240 --> 00:17:49,340
Then it can be me, right?

209
00:17:49,340 --> 00:17:51,920
Hey, let go!

210
00:17:53,790 --> 00:17:55,450
Hey!

211
00:17:55,450 --> 00:17:58,620
If you're doing it with a dude
who sells himself, do it with me instead.

212
00:17:58,620 --> 00:18:00,490
Screw off! Let me go!

213
00:18:00,490 --> 00:18:02,250
Why're you acting like a virgin?

214
00:18:02,250 --> 00:18:04,780
- You're used to this, right?
- Stop!

215
00:18:04,780 --> 00:18:06,840
Stop it!

216
00:18:26,370 --> 00:18:28,570
Akina, are you alright?

217
00:18:28,570 --> 00:18:30,280
Naoki...

218
00:18:32,540 --> 00:18:36,380
The hell? Piss off, man!

219
00:18:37,850 --> 00:18:42,010
Well, I mean... This was a play.

220
00:18:42,010 --> 00:18:43,610
She wanted to do it outside.

221
00:18:43,610 --> 00:18:45,060
Like hell I did.

222
00:18:45,060 --> 00:18:47,470
Says the one buying men for herself.

223
00:18:48,310 --> 00:18:50,780
What's so wrong about that?

224
00:18:50,780 --> 00:18:53,230
I won't have sex with men I don't want to.

225
00:18:53,230 --> 00:18:55,440
I'll pay money to have sex
with the ones I do.

226
00:18:55,440 --> 00:18:57,540
What's so wrong about that?

227
00:18:57,540 --> 00:19:00,780
What's so wrong with living true to myself?

228
00:19:02,710 --> 00:19:06,100
Akina. Let's report him to the police.

229
00:19:12,080 --> 00:19:14,000
H-Haru?

230
00:19:14,990 --> 00:19:16,580
Haru!

231
00:19:16,580 --> 00:19:18,630
Are you okay?

232
00:19:18,630 --> 00:19:19,910
I'm fine.

233
00:19:19,910 --> 00:19:22,580
What about you?

234
00:19:22,580 --> 00:19:24,340
Are you okay?

235
00:19:24,340 --> 00:19:27,900
- I'm totally fine.
- No, you're not.

236
00:19:27,900 --> 00:19:29,810
What a scumbag...

237
00:19:34,840 --> 00:19:36,150
Here, your phone.

238
00:19:36,950 --> 00:19:38,410
Thank you.

239
00:19:38,410 --> 00:19:40,980
Sorry to get you involved in that.

240
00:19:46,040 --> 00:19:48,240
Well...

241
00:19:48,240 --> 00:19:50,560
Thank you for earlier.

242
00:19:51,210 --> 00:19:56,590
Haru answered your phone
when I called to ask why you were late.

243
00:19:56,590 --> 00:19:59,350
She told me you may still be in the area.

244
00:19:59,350 --> 00:20:01,560
I see.

245
00:20:02,460 --> 00:20:04,690
I was right to come and get you.

246
00:20:06,550 --> 00:20:09,070
Then I'll get going.

247
00:20:09,070 --> 00:20:10,540
Please take care of Akina for me.

248
00:20:10,540 --> 00:20:13,860
- Of course.
- Thank you.

249
00:20:51,600 --> 00:20:58,010
Do you do that huffing around Haru, too?

250
00:20:58,010 --> 00:20:59,550
What huffing?

251
00:20:59,550 --> 00:21:06,530
It's that narcissistic pity smirk
you do sometimes.

252
00:21:07,540 --> 00:21:10,460
You're only satisfying yourself doing that.

253
00:21:22,480 --> 00:21:23,950
Why?

254
00:21:24,880 --> 00:21:29,130
I thought I'd made a pathetic excuse.

255
00:21:36,190 --> 00:21:37,910
What happened?

256
00:21:38,550 --> 00:21:40,870
I tripped.

257
00:21:41,960 --> 00:21:44,400
What are you doing?

258
00:21:56,540 --> 00:21:59,410
Where'd I put the first aid kit...

259
00:22:02,020 --> 00:22:05,400
You, why do you trip so much?

260
00:22:06,030 --> 00:22:08,420
Whoops, slipped back into it again.

261
00:22:10,960 --> 00:22:14,220
<i>What's so wrong with living true to myself?</i>

262
00:22:16,000 --> 00:22:17,570
Ouji.

263
00:22:18,340 --> 00:22:22,050
I can't help it, habits are hard to break.

264
00:22:22,050 --> 00:22:23,810
Ouji.

265
00:22:28,240 --> 00:22:32,580
I want to stay with you.

266
00:22:35,300 --> 00:22:37,660
I want us to stay together.

267
00:22:41,200 --> 00:22:42,300
But that's...

268
00:22:42,300 --> 00:22:46,280
I've loved you all this time,
and you finally looked my way,

269
00:22:46,280 --> 00:22:49,880
so why do we have to break up now?

270
00:22:49,880 --> 00:22:52,300
You can't expect anything from me, you know?

271
00:22:52,300 --> 00:22:55,760
